{"type":"message","id":"81a41093","parentId":"51b13f08","timestamp":"2026-05-10T07:02:54.876Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The transcribe function succeeded (text was printed before), but then the process got SIGKILL during cleanup. The issue seems to be that when transcription completes and then cleanup runs, the process gets killed.\n\nWait - actually the output was \"EXIT:124\" which is a timeout exit code. The transcription might have succeeded but the `os.unlink('/tmp/v44.wav')` at the end never ran because timeout killed it. But we DID see text printed in earlier tests... Let me try a simpler approach.\n\nActually, looking back at the process output more carefully - the `poll` returned `EXIT:124` which means `timeout` killed it. But the text was already printed. Let me try running the exact same thing but with the transcription only, no cleanup.\n\n\nSo the transcription is working fine - we're getting the output as \"เช็คดูสิว่าตอนนี้มี process อะไรที่ทำงานอยู่บ้าง\" from the earlier run. The real problem is just that cleanup isn't running after the timeout kills the process, so the temp file is still there. I should try a more efficient approach - maybe keep the model hot in memory and test with a fresh file to see if the transcription speed improves.\n","thinkingSignature":"f23168c79ba3ec0b54cc96139b52ab25c92b89da1d02d4a7b00160d604efdfa9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9ygbof7fmpso_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ffmpeg -i /home/apinan/.openclaw/media/inbound/file_44---0a7e6c51-e1a1-46e3-a23f-d1573e1c9893.ogg -ar 16000 -ac 1 -c:a pcm_s16le /tmp/v44b.wav -y 2>/dev/null && python3 << 'EOF'\nimport sys, os\nsys.path.insert(0, '/home/apinan/.openclaw/plugin-skills/voice-speech/scripts')\nfrom _whisper_manager import transcribe\ntext, info = transcribe('/tmp/v44b.wav')\nprint(text.strip())\nEOF\nrm -f /tmp/v44b.wav","timeout":30,"yieldMs":20000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model