{"type":"message","id":"2b0f8fcc","parentId":"eb639e07","timestamp":"2026-05-10T07:23:04.253Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is really frustrating. The model loads fine but every time I try to transcribe a 28-second file, it gets killed. The model is about 1.5GB. 28 seconds of audio at 16kHz mono PCM is about 896KB, which is tiny. So why does transcription require so much memory that it gets OOM-killed?\n\nLet me check if maybe the issue is the WSL2 memory limit. Looking at the stats: 24GB total, Qdrant uses 3GB, OpenClaw Node uses 521MB, Hermes uses 239MB, Ollama uses 200MB. That's about 4.5GB used.\n \nWait, I'm noticing something odd here—those Python processes from earlier are still lingering even after I killed them, which suggests they might be parent processes or there's some kind of resource contention happening that's eating up memory.\n\nLet me step back and try a different approach entirely. Instead of fighting with the current setup, maybe I should explore using Ollama's whisper integration, or find a lighter-weight transcription model, or even build a streaming approach that processes audio in chunks rather than loading everything into memory at once.\n","thinkingSignature":"e62ad663fa9950716da3bafdd67d35fd120e811cc72f723fc443b2a0095a2044"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_14jq8j17j6wp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ps aux | grep -E \"python3.*whisper\\|python3.*transcribe\" | grep -v grep; echo \"---\"; free -m | head -2"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":188,"output":301,"cacheRead":61440,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61929,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778397768442,"responseId":"064f654970762b710eccb506c9228251"}}
