{"type":"message","id":"dea6b901","parentId":"2d62e052","timestamp":"2026-05-10T07:23:17.653Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good - memory is fine now. The issue isn't memory. Let me look at the SIGKILL reason more carefully. It seems the model.transcribe() call gets killed. Let me check if it's an IO issue - maybe the av library can't read the file properly.\n\nWait, I realize the issue - I'm running these in exec sessions where the parent process (the shell) gets signals that propagate to the Python process. Let me try a completely different approach - use nohup or run the Python script as a background process and wait for it.\n","thinkingSignature":"7c271fa67678382aed4bb18f0f055bb112055f3fc6b6fa04c4d9f548c2e31eeb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6je3m0qhpx1l_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ffmpeg -i /home/apinan/.openclaw/media/inbound/file_47---12a4d6ca-0175-48ed-9961-9a475dbaead2.ogg -ar 16000 -ac 1 -c:a pcm_s16le /tmp/v47g.wav -y 2>/dev/null\ncat > /tmp/t47.py << 'PYEOF'\nfrom faster_whisper import WhisperModel\nimport os, sys\nm = WhisperModel('large-v3-turbo', device='cpu', compute_type='int8', num_workers=1)\ns, i = m.transcribe('/tmp/v47g.wav', beam_size=1, language='th', vad_filter=False)\nsys.stdout.write(''.join(x.text for x in s))\nsys.stdout.flush()\nPYEOF\nls -la /tmp/v47g.wav /tmp/t47.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":239,"output":323,"cacheRead":61504,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62066,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778397784314,"responseId":"064f65594ee7ea1fe033efa5730f9457"}}
