{"type":"message","id":"be27a0ab","parentId":"8b02c78f","timestamp":"2026-05-10T07:28:11.124Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so `v47c1.wav` was deleted (probably by the earlier kill). c2 and c3 still exist. Let me transcribe c2 and c3 first, then figure out c1.\n\nActually wait - c1.wav got deleted. That means the `rm -f /tmp/v47_short.wav` from earlier was for the short file, not c1. But c1 should still exist...\n\nOh wait, actually the previous process that got killed (sharp-falcon) probably deleted c1 and c3 already since it ran with `os.unlink(c)`. But it didn't complete. So:\n- c1 was unlinked but still open by the killed process → file is gone\n\n\n- c3 might still be there though\n\nLet me check what c2 and c3 contain.\n","thinkingSignature":"2b92f66b9b3964dd6a6f15c8aeb0d23d1058a54060aa965675f67b6d867653e7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_upji3gq4wi5s_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nfrom faster_whisper import WhisperModel\nm = WhisperModel('large-v3-turbo', device='cpu', compute_type='int8', num_workers=1)\ns, i = m.transcribe('/tmp/v47c2.wav', beam_size=1, language='th', vad_filter=False)\nprint('c2:', ''.join(x.text for x in s))\n\" && python3 -c \"\nfrom faster_whisper import WhisperModel\nm = WhisperModel('large-v3-turbo', device='cpu', compute_type='int8', num_workers=1)\ns, i = m.transcribe('/tmp/v47c3.wav', beam_size=1, language='th', vad_filter=False)\nprint('c3:', ''.join(x.text for x in s))\n\" && rm -f /tmp/v47c2.wav /tmp/v47c3.wav /tmp/v47c.wav /tmp/v47d.wav /tmp/v47e.wav /tmp/v47f.wav /tmp/v47g.wav","timeout":30,"yieldMs":25000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":460,"output":431,"cacheRead":64256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65147,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778398073194,"responseId":"064f667ab972b88edfaa3fe6f5174032"}}
