{"type":"message","id":"6f2d2172","parentId":"94f30c84","timestamp":"2026-05-10T07:31:50.934Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is also taking too long. The issue is that for long audio files (28 seconds), the transcription process gets killed even though:\n1. There's ~19GB RAM available\n2. The model loads fine (~1.5GB)\n3. Short clips (5-10s) work fine\n\nThe problem might be that for longer audio, the decoding/preprocessing step is more memory intensive, OR there's something about the timeout/kill mechanism that's terminating the process after 25-30 seconds regardless.\n\nWait - I just noticed something. All my previous transcriptions that succeeded were running in sessions that had `yieldMs` set to something, and the process was STILL RUNNING (hadn't exited yet) when I polled. \n\nBut the transcription output never showed up. So maybe those \"successful\" transcriptions I thought worked were actually killed too, and what I saw was just the load message appearing before the process got terminated.\n\nActually, I think I've been misunderstanding the flow. When I run `yieldMs` with a background process and then poll, the process is still executing while I wait. The output I'm seeing at 25-30 seconds isn't the transcription finishing—it's the session timing out. Looking back at file_45's transcription, it exited with code 124 (timeout), but somehow I still got the text afterward. That doesn't make sense unless the polling is returning partial output from a killed process.\n\nLet me retrace: I ran transcribe3.py with a 60-second timeout, it took longer than that, got killed, but then I somehow still have the transcription. The only way this makes sense is if the transcription actually completed successfully but the timeout command itself returned 124 anyway. Or maybe the text was buffered and only flushed when I polled the session.\n\nLooking at the timing for file_47 again - I've tried maybe 10-15 times and it keeps getting killed, whereas file_45 worked on the first try. The difference is file_47 is significantly longer at around 28 seconds of audio.\n\nI'm starting to think there's a cgroup memory limit that triggers an OOM kill after a certain amount of time, or possibly a memory threshold that gets hit specifically with longer audio files. Let me test with a 15-second segment of file_47 to see if there's a threshold where it stops working, though I should probably first check if there's a simpler explanation - maybe the issue is with how I'm handling the model singleton in _whisper_manager itself.\n\nIf the module was imported multiple times with the model already loaded, subsequent imports wouldn't reinitialize `_model`, so `is_loaded()` would correctly return True but transcriptions would fail. But that doesn't quite fit either since the model appears to load successfully.\n\nMaybe the process is getting killed due to a timeout rather than memory - the `timeout` command with SIGKILL after 40 seconds combined with Whisper's own processing time might be triggering the limit. I should try without the timeout wrapper and use Python's internal timing instead. Actually, switching to a different audio format like FLAC could be more efficient than WAV for longer files, or I could try the faster-whisper small model to reduce memory usage.\n\nBut wait - I'm noticing something about the memory footprint. The first successful run was fast because the model was already in the filesystem cache from earlier usage, so it loaded instantly without the expensive deserialization step.\n\nThe subsequent runs had to actually load from disk, and there are multiple Python processes still lingering from failed attempts - one is taking 5.7% memory and another 4.5%. When I tried to kill these zombie processes, they might not have been cleaned up properly by the kernel, and there could be subprocess threads that didn't terminate cleanly.\n\nI should just restart fresh and try again rather than continuing to debug these orphaned processes. Let me start over with a clean state.\n","thinkingSignature":"ba910fceba098c79195085a62c4144070acce1463c63a23a6a604be0868eaecf"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sgftwm7jt88f_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"pkill -9 -f \"t47\\|transcribe4\\|transcribe5\\|v47\" 2>/dev/null; sleep 2\nps aux | grep \"python3\" | grep -v grep | awk '{print $2, $6, $11}'"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":368,"output":863,"cacheRead":65408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66639,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778398262526,"responseId":"064f673844dd5af25517beb692158ae1"}}
