{"type":"message","id":"bc853251","parentId":"73481d7b","timestamp":"2026-05-10T07:40:39.860Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Boss doesn't want to use API or pay more. Then we need to stick with the current approach. But the issue is that long audio files get killed. The workaround of chunking works but is slow.\n\nLet me think about how to make it faster with the chunking approach. Currently each 5-second chunk takes ~15-20s because we're loading the model fresh each time. If I keep the model loaded in RAM, we can process chunks faster.\n\nBut the issue is that even with model loaded, the full 28s audio still gets killed. Let me think...\n\nActually, the SIGKILL happens during transcription, not during model loading. So maybe the issue is memory fragmentation or something else.\n\nWait - I just realized something. When I run the 5-second chunks one by one with fresh model each time, it works. \n\nThe real bottleneck is that reloading the model for each chunk is what's eating up all the time. I need to find a way to keep the model in memory across all the chunk processing. The OOM kills are happening with 28-second audio specifically, so if I can process the 28-second file through the already-loaded model, that should sidestep the memory issues that come from repeated model reloading.\n\nLooking at the SIGKILL pattern, it's not hitting the model loading phase—it's dying during the actual transcription. I suspect PyAv's av.open() is consuming more memory than expected when reading the audio file, possibly due to how the OGG decoder handles memory internally. Let me try a different approach: read the audio into a numpy array first with pydub or librosa, save that array to disk, then transcribe from the array instead of directly from the OGG file. That might avoid the memory pitfalls of the current approach.\n\nActually, I should just stick with the chunked transcription method—splitting into 5-second chunks, transcribing each sequentially with the model in memory, then combining the results. I already have most of the chunks from before, so I can transcribe the remaining ones and get this done.\n","thinkingSignature":"a60e0fbdeb013a144b05ca247724ab5ac322c33c9d03904f88a9e542fdcf1368"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nเข้าใจครับ มึงใช้วิธีตัดช่วงแล้ว process ทีละตอนอยู่แล้ว มันทำงานได้แต่ต้องรอ\n\nให้ผมเพิ่ม auto-chunking ใน skill ให้ทำงานอัตโนมัติ ไม่ต้องรอนานขนาดนี้ แต่ถอดเสียงยาวๆ ก็จะช้ากว่าย่นๆ อยู่แล้วครับ 🧑🏼‍💻"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":11612,"output":611,"cacheRead":57280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69503,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778398804686,"responseId":"064f695674c81d9ff3ec939ff67609b8"}}
