{"type":"message","id":"45ae5afd","parentId":"2440f2e6","timestamp":"2026-05-10T07:43:58.568Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The model IS loaded (1.5GB in RAM) but it still gets killed when trying to transcribe. The transcribe step itself is what's being killed, not the model loading. The issue is that even with the model in RAM, the transcription process itself uses too much memory when processing a 28s file.\n\nLet me try a different approach - pre-split the file into 10s chunks and do them one by one, loading/unloading the model between each. Or better yet, just have the chunking script do it correctly by loading the model once and transcribing each chunk separately.\n\nWait, but I set `beam_size=1` which is already the minimum. The issue might be that the CTranslate2 library is loading additional memory during the actual transcription.\n \nMemory-wise, after the model loads at 1.5GB, I've got about 17GB available, so theoretically there should be room. The problem might be something specific to this particular file or how it's being processed. Let me test with a shorter 10s clip to see if that works fine and narrow down whether the issue is file length or something else.\n","thinkingSignature":"c53e408788976cf46a1b56a8defceb95f9a3f1a70d06eaf514d9050a0cf40df4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_onqimf8kqx8l_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"pkill -9 -f \"python3.*whisper\\|python3.*v47\" 2>/dev/null; sleep 2\nffmpeg -i /home/apinan/.openclaw/media/inbound/file_47---12a4d6ca-0175-48ed-9961-9a475dbaead2.ogg -ss 0 -t 10 -ar 16000 -ac 1 -c:a pcm_s16le /tmp/short10.wav -y 2>/dev/null\nls -la /tmp/short10.wav\npython3 -c \"\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, '/home/apinan/.openclaw/plugin-skills/voice-speech/scripts')\nfrom _whisper_manager import transcribe\ntext, info = transcribe('/tmp/short10.wav')\nprint(text.strip())\n\" && rm -f /tmp/short10.wav","timeout":20,"yieldMs":15000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provid