{"type":"message","id":"cde181bb","parentId":"66a8dd2f","timestamp":"2026-05-10T07:46:44.578Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cgroups show `max` for all relevant slices, so there's no memory limit set at the cgroup level. So why is the process getting SIGKILL?\n\nWait - the model is ALREADY loaded (from a previous run). When we call `is_loaded()` it returns True. But then when we try to transcribe, it gets killed. This means the model IS in memory but the transcription step itself uses too much memory.\n\nLet me try a different approach - use the already-loaded model from `_model` variable. The issue might be that each transcription creates temporary tensors that exceed available memory when the model is already loaded.\n\nLet me try calling transcribe directly on the already-loaded model without going through the module reload.\n","thinkingSignature":"85dd168b58f33100604c65b2224d9207b12a81d84ba23ee7841697ae5249f2fe"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dn7brj74rlsx_1","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"nova-harbor","timeout":5000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":647,"output":197,"cacheRead":72576,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73420,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778399194199,"responseId":"064f6adba536460d85f544d71cb426e1"}}
