ages.tts`, so keep shared provider credentials and fallback policy in `messages.tts` and set only persona-specific values such as provider, voice, model, style, or auto mode here.\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-agents.md:    tts: {\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-agents.md:      prefsPath: \"~/.openclaw/settings/tts.json\",\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-agents.md:          voiceId: \"voice_id\",\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-agents.md:          voiceSettings: {\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-agents.md:          voice: \"en-US-AvaMultilingualNeural\",\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-agents.md:          model: \"gpt-4o-mini-tts\",\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-agents.md:          voice: \"alloy\",\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-agents.md:- `auto` controls the default auto-TTS mode: `off`, `always`, `inbound`, or `tagged`. `/tts on|off` can override local prefs, and `/tts status` shows the effective state.\n/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-agents.md:- When `providers.openai.baseUrl` points to a non-OpenAI endpoint, OpenClaw treats it as an OpenAI-compatible TTS server and relaxes model/voice validation.","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778400164035}}
{"type":"message","id":"2a9a9f22","parentId":"961bbb1f","timestamp":"2026-05-10T08:02:51.171Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the TTS config documentation more carefully to understand what's available.\n","thinkingSignature":"6d3b1691137a36ba326061e02eb37690676cd766c5d33315152289a4682a6977"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hjbncz13imfy_1","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":80,"path":"/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-agents.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1085,"output":69,"cacheRead":86912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88066,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778400164040,"responseId":"064f6ea538fba15ce595ac777fb8cda9"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4ec6e068","parentId":"2a9a9f22","timestamp":"2026-05-10T08:02:51.181Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hjbncz13imfy_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nsummary: \"Agent defaults, multi-agent routing, session, messages, and talk config\"\nread_when:\n  - Tuning agent defaults (models, thinking, workspace, heartbeat, media, skills)\n  - Configuring multi-agent routing and bindings\n  - Adjusting session, message delivery, and talk-mode behavior\ntitle: \"Configuration — agents\"\n---\n\nAgent-scoped configuration keys under `agents.*`, `multiAgent.*`, `session.*`,\n`messages.*`, and `talk.*`. For channels, tools, gateway runtime, and other\ntop-level keys, see [Configuration reference](/gateway/configuration-reference).\n\n## Agent defaults\n\n### `agents.defaults.workspace`\n\nDefault: `~/.openclaw/workspace`.\n\n```json5\n{\n  agents: { defaults: { workspace: \"~/.openclaw/workspace\" } },\n}\n```\n\n### `agents.defaults.repoRoot`\n\nOptional repository root shown in the system prompt's Runtime line. If unset, OpenClaw auto-detects by walking upward from the workspace.\n\n```json5\n{\n  agents: { defaults: { repoRoot: \"~/Projects/openclaw\" } },\n}\n```\n\n### `agents.defaults.skills`\n\nOptional default skill allowlist for agents that do not set\n`agents.list[].skills`.\n\n```json5\n{\n  agents: {\n    defaults: { skills: [\"github\", \"weather\"] },\n    list: [\n      { id: \"writer\" }, // inherits github, weather\n      { id: \"docs\", skills: [\"docs-search\"] }, // replaces defaults\n      { id: \"locked-down\", skills: [] }, // no skills\n    ],\n  },\n}\n```\n\n- Omit `agents.defaults.skills` for unrestricted skills by default.\n- Omit `agents.list[].skills` to inherit the defaults.\n- Set `agents.list[].skills: []` for no skills.\n- A non-empty `agents.list[].skills` list is the final set for that agent; it\n  does not merge with defaults.\n\n### `agents.defaults.skipBootstrap`\n\nDisables automatic creation of workspace bootstrap files (`AGENTS.md`, `SOUL.md`, `TOOLS.md`, `IDENTITY.md`, `USER.md`, `HEARTBEAT.md`, `BOOTSTRAP.md`).\n\n```json5\n{\n  agents: { defaults: { skipBootstrap: true } },\n}\n```\n\n### `agents.defaults.skipOptionalBootstrapFiles`\n\nSkips creation of selected optional workspace files while still writing required bootstrap files. Valid values: `SOUL.md`, `USER.md`, `HEARTBEAT.md`, and `IDENTITY.md`.\n\n```json5\n{\n  agents: {\n    defaults: {\n      skipOptionalBootstrapFiles: [\"SOUL.md\", \"USER.md\"],\n    },\n  },\n\n[1329 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778400171181}}
{"type":"message","id":"91b1005e","parentId":"4ec6e068","timestamp":"2026-05-10T08:02:57.784Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me look at the TTS config section more specifically.\n","thinkingSignature":"9bae561467512c4351af650116c64b014587c626182b25fff9697a890ac6c179"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h59kp88fzfme_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"tts\\|voice\\|messages.tts\\|messages.tts\" /home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-agents.md | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":776,"output":77,"cacheRead":87872,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88725,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778400171185,"responseId":"064f6eac92a36f8ce379aa32ae1c2074"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ab99fe61","parentId":"91b1005e","timestamp":"2026-05-10T08:02:57.811Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_h59kp88fzfme_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"940:Use `agents.list[].tts` to give an agent its own TTS provider, voice, model,\n942:`messages.tts`, so shared credentials can stay in one place while individual\n943:agents override only the voice or provider fields they need. The active agent's\n944:override applies to automatic spoken replies, `/tts audio`, `/tts status`, and\n945:the `tts` agent tool. See [Text-to-speech](/tools/tts#per-agent-voice-overrides)\n964:        tts: {\n966:            elevenlabs: { voiceId: \"EXAVITQu4vr4xnSDxMaL\" },\n1004:- `tts`: optional per-agent text-to-speech overrides. The block deep-merges over `messages.tts`, so keep shared provider credentials and fallback policy in `messages.tts` and set only persona-specific values such as provider, voice, model, style, or auto mode here.\n1307:    tts: {\n1315:      prefsPath: \"~/.openclaw/settings/tts.json\",\n1320:          voiceId: \"voice_id\",\n1325:          voiceSettings: {\n1334:          voice: \"en-US-AvaMultilingualNeural\",\n1341:          model: \"gpt-4o-mini-tts\",\n1342:          voice: \"alloy\",\n1350:- `auto` controls the default auto-TTS mode: `off`, `always`, `inbound`, or `tagged`. `/tts on|off` can override local prefs, and `/tts status` shows the effective state.\n1356:- When `providers.openai.baseUrl` points to a non-OpenAI endpoint, OpenClaw treats it as an OpenAI-compatible TTS server and relaxes model/voice validation.\n1370:        voiceId: \"elevenlabs_voice_id\",\n1371:        voiceAliases: {\n1392:- Legacy flat Talk keys (`talk.voiceId`, `talk.voiceAliases`, `talk.modelId`, `talk.outputFormat`, `talk.apiKey`) are compatibility-only and are auto-migrated into `talk.providers.<provider>`.\n1396:- `providers.*.voiceAliases` lets Talk directives use friendly names.\n1398:- macOS MLX playback runs through the bundled `openclaw-mlx-tts` helper when present, or an executable on `PATH`; `OPENCLAW_MLX_TTS_BIN` overrides the helper path for development."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":16,"aggregated":"940:Use `agents.list[].tts` to give an agent its own TTS provider, voice, model,\n942:`messages.tts`, so shared credentials can stay in one place while individual\n943:agents override only the voice or provider fields they need. The active agent's\n944:override applies to automatic spoken replies, `/tts audio`, `/tts status`, and\n945:the `tts` agent tool. See [Text-to-speech](/tools/tts#per-agent-voice-overrides)\n964:        tts: {\n966:            elevenlabs: { voiceId: \"EXAVITQu4vr4xnSDxMaL\" },\n1004:- `tts`: optional per-agent text-to-speech overrides. The block deep-merges over `messages.tts`, so keep shared provider credentials and fallback policy in `messages.tts` and set only persona-specific values such as provider, voice, model, style, or auto mode here.\n1307:    tts: {\n1315:      prefsPath: \"~/.openclaw/settings/tts.json\",\n1320:          voiceId: \"voice_id\",\n1325:          voiceSettings: {\n1334:          voice: \"en-US-AvaMultilingualNeural\",\n1341:          model: \"gpt-4o-mini-tts\",\n1342:          voice: \"alloy\",\n1350:- `auto` controls the default auto-TTS mode: `off`, `always`, `inbound`, or `tagged`. `/tts on|off` can override local prefs, and `/tts status` shows the effective state.\n1356:- When `providers.openai.baseUrl` points to a non-OpenAI endpoint, OpenClaw treats it as an OpenAI-compatible TTS server and relaxes model/voice validation.\n1370:        voiceId: \"elevenlabs_voice_id\",\n1371:        voiceAliases: {\n1392:- Legacy flat Talk keys (`talk.voiceId`, `talk.voiceAliases`, `talk.modelId`, `talk.outputFormat`, `talk.apiKey`) are compatibility-only and are auto-migrated into `talk.providers.<provider>`.\n1396:- `providers.*.voiceAliases` lets Talk directives use friendly names.\n1398:- macOS MLX playback runs through the bundled `openclaw-mlx-tts` helper when present, or an executable on `PATH`; `OPENCLAW_MLX_TTS_BIN` overrides the helper path for development.","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778400177811}}
{"type":"message","id":"21ef480f","parentId":"ab99fe61","timestamp":"2026-05-10T08:03:05.881Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me look at the TTS docs more specifically, especially the providers that are supported and the local TTS options.\n","thinkingSignature":"6549999f9e14ac098b9dcdefd8eb6f00bdbffd303b1b43ac25972d1d573f0038"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_84nc7ijryn7p_1","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":60,"offset":1300,"path":"/home/apinan/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-agents.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":670,"output":89,"cacheRead":88576,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":89335,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778400177816,"responseId":"064f6eb3711316469a6ad5d8888f0360"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ff1dddba","parentId":"21ef480f","timestamp":"2026-05-10T08:03:05.888Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_84nc7ijryn7p_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Batches rapid text-only messages from the same sender into a single agent turn. Media/attachments flush immediately. Control commands bypass debouncing.\n\n### TTS (text-to-speech)\n\n```json5\n{\n  messages: {\n    tts: {\n      auto: \"always\", // off | always | inbound | tagged\n      mode: \"final\", // final | all\n      provider: \"elevenlabs\",\n      summaryModel: \"openai/gpt-4.1-mini\",\n      modelOverrides: { enabled: true },\n      maxTextLength: 4000,\n      timeoutMs: 30000,\n      prefsPath: \"~/.openclaw/settings/tts.json\",\n      providers: {\n        elevenlabs: {\n          apiKey: \"elevenlabs_api_key\",\n          baseUrl: \"https://api.elevenlabs.io\",\n          voiceId: \"voice_id\",\n          modelId: \"eleven_multilingual_v2\",\n          seed: 42,\n          applyTextNormalization: \"auto\",\n          languageCode: \"en\",\n          voiceSettings: {\n            stability: 0.5,\n            similarityBoost: 0.75,\n            style: 0.0,\n            useSpeakerBoost: true,\n            speed: 1.0,\n          },\n        },\n        microsoft: {\n          voice: \"en-US-AvaMultilingualNeural\",\n          lang: \"en-US\",\n          outputFormat: \"audio-24khz-48kbitrate-mono-mp3\",\n        },\n        openai: {\n          apiKey: \"openai_api_key\",\n          baseUrl: \"https://api.openai.com/v1\",\n          model: \"gpt-4o-mini-tts\",\n          voice: \"alloy\",\n        },\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n- `auto` controls the default auto-TTS mode: `off`, `always`, `inbound`, or `tagged`. `/tts on|off` can override local prefs, and `/tts status` shows the effective state.\n- `summaryModel` overrides `agents.defaults.model.primary` for auto-summary.\n- `modelOverrides` is enabled by default; `modelOverrides.allowProvider` defaults to `false` (opt-in).\n- API keys fall back to `ELEVENLABS_API_KEY`/`XI_API_KEY` and `OPENAI_API_KEY`.\n- Bundled speech providers are plugin-owned. If `plugins.allow` is set, include each TTS provider plugin you want to use, for example `microsoft` for Edge TTS. The legacy `edge` provider id is accepted as an alias for `microsoft`.\n- `providers.openai.baseUrl` overrides the OpenAI TTS endpoint. Resolution order is config, then `OPENAI_TTS_BASE_URL`, then `https://api.openai.com/v1`.\n- When `providers.openai.baseUrl` points to a non-OpenAI endpoint, OpenClaw treats it as an OpenAI-compatible TTS server and relaxes model/voice validation.\n\n---\n\n\n[50 more lines in file. Use offset=1360 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778400185888}}
{"type":"message","id":"23799b21","parentId":"ff1dddba","timestamp":"2026-05-10T08:03:32.098Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So OpenClaw supports TTS with providers: elevenlabs, microsoft, openai. It does NOT natively support local TTS models like Kokoro, Piper, etc.\n\nHowever, the key insight is: if I set `providers.openai.baseUrl` to a local server, OpenClaw will treat it as an OpenAI-compatible TTS server. So I could:\n\n1. Run a local TTS server (like a Kokoro HTTP server) \n2. Point OpenClaw's `providers.openai.baseUrl` to it\n3. Use it like OpenAI TTS\n\n\n4. Kokoro-ONNX has a Gradio web interface built in that could serve as that local server, which would let me leverage the Thai voice models I found earlier\n\nLet me explore this approach further.\n\nActually, wait—the real question here is what the user is trying to accomplish. They want a Thai male voice that sounds natural and similar to Google's Gemini, which is a high bar. I should focus on what they actually need rather than getting sidetracked with the OpenClaw configuration details.\n\nLet me look into the F5-TTS option since that was mentioned as supporting Thai.\n\nActually, the most practical path forward is to test Kokoro-ONNX with Thai voices first since it's straightforward to set up locally. I can use it as a local server and configure OpenClaw to use it. If that doesn't work well, I could also explore OpenAI's TTS API or ElevenLabs' voice library, which has some Thai voice options available. Let me start by checking what Thai voice options are actually available with Kokoro-ONNX and setting those up.\n","thinkingSignature":"d102e0190b5dd51242345fbb5ebd205ce23546d24fad89f96c88422776123fbc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ie8blc90kms4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nfrom kokoro_tts import Kokoro\nk = Kokoro('/tmp/kokoro-v1.0.onnx', '/tmp/voices.bin')\nvoices = k.get_voices()\nprint('Total:', len(voices))\nfor v in voices:\n    print(v)\n\" 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":807,"output":438,"cacheRead":89152,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90397,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778400185893,"responseId":"064f6ebb13d850f8a86f7307f42295ec"}}
