{"type":"message","id":"e4fd3d31","parentId":"8820bd09","timestamp":"2026-05-10T08:03:54.732Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Kokoro only has 54 voices and none are Thai. But it has multilingual support with `cmn` (Mandarin) and `en` voices. It can't do Thai.\n\nLet me think about what's actually achievable on this machine:\n\n1. **Piper TTS** - No Thai voices in the official repo\n2. **Coqui TTS / XTTSv2** - Would need to download large models and likely has the same OOM issues\n3. **f5-tts-thai** - Requires proper installation, may have dependencies issues\n4. **espeakng** - Has Thai support but sounds very robotic\n5. **pyttsx3** - Uses system TTS, might have Thai voices installed\n\n\n6. **System TTS (speech-dispatcher/sapi)** - Could have Thai voices\n\nI should check if the system itself has Thai TTS capabilities through speech-dispatcher or Windows SAPI. The voice messages the boss is hearing are coming from the TTS system, so I need to find what's actually installed. I'm also wondering if there are other OpenClaw TTS providers I haven't explored yet.\n","thinkingSignature":"d49ab8a1278498801fcbf8fff1971c4a7cdf90535e738291fbe64722ef0427a8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yrwqvm1id9g3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport speechd\nclient = speechd.SSIPClient('test')\nprint([s for s in dir(client) if not s.startswith('_')])\nclient.close()\n\" 2>&1; apt list --installed 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"speech\\|espeak\\|festival\\|mbrola\" | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":453,"output":332,"cacheRead":89856,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90641,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778400214033,"responseId":"064f6ed7c8f2e07f7a8a28a94a2aa263"}}
