{"type":"message","id":"77e4863a","parentId":"abf1f4c5","timestamp":"2026-05-10T08:11:42.508Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The lunarlist Thai TTS model is a Tacotron2 model from 2023. I need to check how to run it - it might be a PyTorch model that needs proper installation.\n\nLet me try to download and test the ThaiTTS models. But first, let me think about what's practical:\n\n1. **thaitts-onnx** from PyThaiNLP - ONNX model but the repo says it's locked/can't export to ONNX\n2. **lunarlist/tts-thai-last-step** - seems to be a model but needs NeMo\n3. **Piper TTS** - has Thai voices but none are male (according to the voice list we saw earlier)\n\n\n4. **Google-style Thai male TTS** - not available locally for free\n\nI'm thinking the best approach here is to generate samples from whatever free options I can get working - Microsoft Edge TTS through OpenClaw, pythaitts with the facebook/mms-tts-concat model, and maybe some others - then let the user pick what sounds best. But the th-TH-NiwatNeural voice on Linux might not match the Windows quality, so I should check what Thai voices are actually available on the Microsoft provider.\n\nLet me also look into whether there are any F5-TTS Thai models or MMS-TTS models with Thai voices on Hugging Face that I could try.\n","thinkingSignature":"8c5b7561f0ea111ae328396d035a5dcf7d393f03bee58caab0f7969e987f1a36"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hx8hu1tgcq8b_1","name":"web_search","arguments":{"count":5,"query":"site:huggingface.co Thai TTS male voice natural download free"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1104,"output":333,"cacheRead":95872,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":97309,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778400684634,"responseId":"064f70ad23aeb76540a8f7a967ccfddf"}}
