{"type":"message","id":"340753f9","parentId":"c977bb2d","timestamp":"2026-05-10T08:18:23.114Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The boss said the MMS-TTS voice quality is terrible and doesn't want it. Let me try other options. Let me search for more Thai TTS options, specifically ones that might sound better - like voice cloning models or higher quality models.\n\nLet me try:\n1. F5-TTS-THAI which does voice cloning\n2. Kokoro with a Thai voice pack if available\n3. Speechify or other commercial ones (but boss said no paid)\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The boss mentioned \"Gemini in Google\" sounds good. Google's Thai TTS is actually quite good. But boss doesn't want to pay.\n\n\nI should explore open-source alternatives that might have better voice quality - Voice cloning models like F5-TTS-THAI or Coqui XTTS v2 could potentially work with a Thai reference voice, or I could look into Bark which has some multi-lingual capabilities that might include Thai.\n\nBut honestly, I think the most straightforward path is just to try several different TTS models and let the boss pick whichever one sounds best - downloading and testing a few candidates directly would be faster than searching for the perfect option. Thai male voices available for TTS. \n\nSince boss wants free + male + Thai + natural, let me think about what's actually realistic:\n1. **F5-TTS-THAI** - voice cloning, needs reference audio\n2. **xtts-v2** - voice cloning, needs reference audio\n3. **VITS-mms-thai** - the one I just tried, boss said bad quality\n4. **Kokoro** - no Thai voices built-in\n5. **Piper** - no Thai voices in the repository (checked earlier, th folder doesn't exist in piper-voices)\n6. **Coqui TTS** - might have Thai\n\nLet me check if there are any VITS or YourTTS models for Thai on HuggingFace that I haven't explored yet. MMS-TTS-THAI-MALE-NARRATOR\" and \"VIZINTZOR/F5-TTS-THAI\". F5-TTS is voice cloning though, which needs reference audio. \n\nWhat if I try to create a voice clone of a Thai male voice? I could look for a Thai voice sample and use F5-TTS or XTTS to clone it. But that might be too complex.\n\nLet me just be honest with the boss and say that quality open-source Thai TTS for male voices is very limited, and the best options are either voice cloning (needs reference audio) or cloud services (costs money).\n\nI could also try Elevenlabs' free tier - they have some Thai voices available and a free tier. Or check if Microsoft Edge TTS has a better Thai male voice than what's currently configured.\n\nActually, the current config is using `th-TH-NiwatNeural` which should be a Thai male voice, but maybe it's not configured properly for Linux, so I should suggest trying different Microsoft Thai voices to see if another one sounds better.\n","thinkingSignature":"d202a14291689470ea9bae0d6fbf66af6495655e7e6c4a6df6ef2ba41262a103"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n🧑🏼‍💻 ขอโทษครับ ตัวนั้นคุณภาพแย่จริงๆ\n\nลองหาตัวอื่นมาให้ครับ — กำลังเช็คเพิ่ม\n\n**ปัญหา:** Thai TTS male แบบฟรี + คุณภาพดี หายากมาก ตัวที่เจอส่วนใหญ่เป็น:\n- Voice cloning (ต้องมีเสียงต้นแบบ)\n- Concat TTS (คุณภาพต่ำ)\n- Cloud ต้องเสียตัว\n\nรอแป๊บนะครับ 🧑🏼‍💻"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":11865,"output":839,"cacheRead":92544,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":105248,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778401057491,"responseId":"064f722358a674b3c48cf6189437add6"}}
