{"type":"message","id":"961bdffe","parentId":"1c12b38c","timestamp":"2026-05-10T08:20:23.089Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The boss wants more options. Let me think about what else is available:\n\n1. **Kokoro TTS** - already have it, but no Thai voices. Could potentially use a Thai voice pack if one exists\n2. **Piper TTS** - has voices but I couldn't find Thai ones in the list\n3. **Coqui TTS / XTTS-v2** - supports voice cloning, could clone from a Thai male voice sample. But needs a reference audio.\n4. **F5-TTS-THAI** - voice cloning, same issue\n5. **Typhoon TTS** - Thai startup, has API but costs money\n6. **Google Cloud TTS** - not free, but has Thai male neural voices\n\n\n7. **ElevenLabs** - voice cloning from any audio, could use a Thai male sample\n8. **Microsoft Azure TTS** - already using it but the neural voices aren't great on Linux\n\nI should explore Kokoro TTS more thoroughly since I already have it installed - maybe I can find or create a Thai voice for it. For Kokoro, voices are ONNX files, and there's a Thai voice variant that might work.\n\nI could also try generating a Thai male voice using F5-TTS or XTTS-v2 by providing a Thai male reference audio. Let me first test whether ElevenLabs' free tier includes any Thai voices or if I should search HuggingFace more carefully for a Kokoro Thai voice file. MMS-TTS on its own doesn't seem promising since it's primarily designed for speech synthesis rather than high-quality Thai TTS.\n","thinkingSignature":"abc5ec8f5c8ad57db5f66f7401b56dd5b876ea6be5b4f944108cdd0fc1c64a12"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_z68i5oqvr8hm_1","name":"web_search","arguments":{"count":8,"query":"kokoro TTS Thai voice pack download 2025"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_z68i5oqvr8hm_2","name":"web_search","arguments":{"count":8,"query":"Thai TTS male natural sounding free open source 2025 best"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","us