{"type":"message","id":"9341eb7e","parentId":"9a68a684","timestamp":"2026-05-10T08:20:46.864Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check the free.ai Thai TTS - it says it uses Kokoro and has Thai voices. Let me also try to use the Kokoro model with Thai phonemes - maybe there's a way to generate Thai with Kokoro even though it wasn't designed for Thai.\n\nAlso, let me check the aibase MMS-TTS-THAI-MALE-V1 which says it's fine-tuned from Play.ht data - that might be better quality.\n\nActually, let me think about what's realistic:\n1. The MMS-TTS-THAI-MALE-NARRATOR I already tried was VitsModel and sounded bad\n2. Kokoro doesn't have Thai voices built-in\n\n\n3. Piper doesn't have Thai voices available\n4. Coqui XTTS v2 could potentially handle Thai with the right voice\n5. The aibase model is the same VitsModel architecture and probably won't sound much better\n6. SpeechGen.io and similar services are cloud-based, so they won't work offline\n\nI think the best path forward is to try generating a voice sample with Kokoro using Thai phonemes to see if it can even produce Thai sounds at all, even if the quality isn't great.\n","thinkingSignature":"cef46a752543e74e640029036e7f4308ace11eece420564d4eec4de30b73c7fc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_aw7c4gkqgtsb_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nfrom kokoro_tts import Kokoro\nk = Kokoro('/tmp/kokoro-v1.0.onnx', '/tmp/voices.bin')\n# Try with mixed Thai phonemes / English voices that might sound more natural\nvoices = k.get_voices()\n# Check what languages each voice supports\nfor v in ['am_adam', 'am_eric', 'am_michael', 'bm_daniel', 'bm_george', 'bm_lewis']:\n    print(v)\n\" 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":32984,"output":381,"cacheRead":75328,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":108693,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","time