{"type":"message","id":"35a13481","parentId":"257391d8","timestamp":"2026-05-10T08:22:01.233Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So Microsoft Edge TTS only has one Thai male voice: `th-TH-NiwatNeural`, which is already what's configured in OpenClaw. And apparently that voice quality isn't great either.\n\nThe options are very limited for Thai TTS. Let me think about what's actually usable:\n\n1. **Microsoft Edge TTS (th-TH-NiwatNeural)** - Male Thai, but boss says it's not good quality\n2. **MMS-TTS-THAI-MALE** - We tested, quality was bad\n3. **Kokoro** - No Thai voices built-in\n4. **Piper** - No Thai voices at all (checked earlier)\n\n\n5. **Typhoon** - Need to apply for access\n\nFor free Thai male TTS with decent quality, I'm really hitting a wall. The MMS-TTS model from aibase might work better if I can fetch the actual model files instead of just config, so let me try downloading those directly from Hugging Face.\n","thinkingSignature":"2c7b6159076cb9b3eb435240bbfdcbbcf6cb8d2b41cf27f0c5ad1399e6c1412b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_klet538nbh0x_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nfrom transformers import AutoModel, AutoTokenizer\nimport torch\nimport warnings, os\nwarnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\nos.environ['HF_HUB_DISABLE_XREPO'] = '0'\n\n# Try the v1 version\ntry:\n    model = AutoModel.from_pretrained('VIZINTZOR/MMS-TTS-THAI-MALE-NARRATOR-v1')\n    tok = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained('VIZINTZOR/MMS-TTS-THAI-MALE-NARRATOR-v1')\n    print('v1 loaded OK')\n    print(type(model))\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print('v1 error:', str(e)[:200])\n\" 2>&1 | grep -v \"Warning\\|HF_HUB\\|huggingface\\|download\\|CUDA\\|LOAD REPORT\\|discriminator\\|UNEXPECTED\\|Notes\\|Key\\|Status\\|can be ignored\"","timeout":120,"yieldMs":90000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":292,"output":434,"cacheRead":108864,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109590,"cost":{"