{"type":"message","id":"976bdec1","parentId":"08b78c0d","timestamp":"2026-05-10T08:34:38.377Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me try a different approach. The user is asking about \"Thai TTS 5\" that I had found earlier. Looking back at the conversation, the 5 Thai TTS options I found were:\n\n1. Kokoro-TTS - ONNX 82M, no Thai voices in voices.bin\n2. PyThaiTTS - needs training\n3. MMS-TTS (facebook) - concat, low quality\n4. F5-TTS-THAI - voice cloning, needs reference audio\n5. Typhoon-TTS - Thai product, needs API key\n\nBut maybe the user is referring to something else. \n\nActually, I think the user might be asking about the MMS-TTS-THAI-MALE-V1 model that was on aibase. Looking at what I actually have available, the free Thai TTS options are pretty limited - gTTS gives me a female voice, MMS-TTS-THAI-MALE-NARRATOR gives me a male voice but with poor quality, and PyThaiTTS requires training from scratch.\n\nFor the V1 version, it seems like it was trained on Thai data from Play.ht which should be higher quality, but I can't access it without authentication. I'm wondering if I should try using MeloTTS instead, which might have Thai language support, or fall back to edge-tts with the Microsoft voice that's already working on Linux. Let me investigate whether there are other Thai voice options available through edge-tts that I haven't fully explored yet, or if I should just try running the male VITS English model to see if it handles Thai text adequately.\n","thinkingSignature":"bb8731ac48b986190e33a5711d7549851928d876313ac2acee37505abe846f6f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8fieodg918n7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if there are any Thai voice packs for Kokoro on HF\npython3 -c \"\nfrom huggingface_hub import list_models\nmodels = list(list_models(search='thai tts', sort='downloads', direction=-1, limit=10))\nfor m in models:\n    print(m.id, m.downloads)\n\" 2>&1 | head -20","timeout":15}}],